Your problem is caused by this statement:

```lang-java
public class SqliteDB {
    SqliteDB program = new SqliteDB();
    ...
}
```

While the class SqliteDB gets instantiated, the field `program` is created and assigned to a new SqliteDB class, which has a field `program` which gets created and assigned to a new SqliteDB class, and so on until a stack overflow occurs.

